Contest Elevator Logic

Inputs:
  1) Up and Down latched hi buttons for Floors 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5
    which means they get set by user and stay set until elevator
    state logic clears them
  2) Elevator choose floor latched hi buttons 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5
    which means they get set by user and stay set until elevator
    state logic clears them
  3) Clock which means the user tells the elevator to
    consider the inputs and calculate the next state
  4) Reset tells the elevator to go to floor one, clear all inputs
    Elevator state variables:
    1) Current Floor which is one of 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5
    2) Current Direction Up, Down, or Idle
    3) Button State for all buttons 1 or 0
      1 (hi) = user pressed button
      0 (lo) = elevator logic cleared


Elevator state logic:

  Elevator only considers logic if clocked.

  This means users selects something or calls function that says
    something like "GO!" after pressing Up Down and/or Floor buttons.

  In all states if Reset then:
    Elevator Floor = 0
    Direction = Idle
    All Buttons = 0

  If Direction is Idle then:
    If any button is pressed then does one of these with this priority:
      // check current floor
      1) goes to current floor with floor button (to open door to let someone out)

      // going up has priority over going down
      2) goes to nearest higher floor with up button or floor button pressed
         (may want to go to same floor and clear up button if someone pressed it again)
      3) goes to nearest lower floor with down button or floor button pressed
         (may want to go to same floor and clear down button if someone pressed it again)
      4) goes to highest floor with down button pressed
         (may want to go to same floor and clear down button if someone pressed it again)
      5) goes to lowest floor with up button button pressed
         (may want to go to same floor and clear up button if someone pressed it again)

    If no button is pressed
      1) does nothing and leaves direction as Idle

  If Direction is Up then:
    If any button is pressed then does one of these with this priority:
      // check current floor
      1) goes to current floor with floor button (to open door to let someone out)

      // keep going up mode
      2) goes to nearest higher floor with up, or floor button pressed
        (not including down so it will skip going down people until it is going down)
        (may want to go to same floor and clear up button if someone pressed it again)
      3) goes to highest floor with down button pressed
        (may want to go to same floor and clear up button if someone pressed it again)

      // switch to going down mode
      4) goes to nearest lower floor with down, or floor button pressed
        (not including up so it will skip going up people until it is going up)
         (may want to go to same floor and clear down button if someone pressed it again)
      5) goes to lowest floor with up button button pressed
         (may want to go to same floor and clear down button if someone pressed it again)

    If no button is pressed
      6) does nothing (or could go floor 0) and sets Direction to Idle 

If Direction is Down then:
  If any button is pressed then does one of these with this priority:
    // check current floor
      1) goes to current floor with floor button (to open door to let someone out)

    // keep going down mode
      2) goes to nearest lower floor with down, or floor button pressed
        (not including up so it will skip going up people until it is going up)
      3) goes to lowest floor with up button button pressed

    // switch to going up mode
      4) goes to nearest higher floor with up, or floor button pressed
        (not including down so it will skip going down people until it is going down)
      5) goes to highest floor with down button pressed

    6) goes to nearest higher floor with down button or floor button pressed
  If no button is pressed
    7) does nothing and sets Direction to Idle

When elevator arrives at a new floor then:
  1) clear the floor button for that floor
  2) If the elevator was going up, clear the up button for that floor because you are picking 
       up the going up people.
  3) If the elevator was going down, clear the down button for that floor because you are picking
       up the going down people.
  4) If the elevator goes back to the same floor:
     This means either:
      1) someone pressed the floor button for the same floor to get out 
           (want to keep same direction, clear button for that direction again just in case it got pressed again)
      2) elevator answered up button but no higher floors were pressed and the down button
        was also pressed. (want to change direction to down, clear down button)
      3) elevator answered down button but no lower floors were pressed and the up button
        was also pressed. (want to change direction to up, clear up button)
  5) Elevator state = door open waiting
    

When elevator leaves an old floor to go to a new floor then:
  1) If new floor is higher than old floor then new direction = up and elevator state = door closed travelling
  2) If new floor is lower than old floor then new direction = down and elevator state = door closed travelling
  3) If new floor is same as the old floor then it doesn't matter what the direction is..
    direction will be figured out when the elevator moves again... (elevator has arrived again... door open waiting)
   
         
When elevator has no floor to go to then direction = idle (this means all buttons are clear) and
  elevator state = door closed idle

